Mais um dia de cuidado com minha beleza com a equipe maravilhosa da @casaewa___ 
Resolvi fazer o cabelo antes de voltar pra casa em NY e fui recebida tão bem!
Conversando com a Débora, criadora da casa, percebi a importância de espaços de beleza que valorizem não só nossa essência ancestral, mas também profissionais que são na sua própria essência honestas no desejo de cuidar e acolher nossas inseguranças. Como alguém que já sofreu tanto preconceito e tratamentos equivocados em espaços de beleza sem preparo e sem interesse em se preparar e diversificar seu público, da gatilho ir no salão aqui no Brasil. Me sinto como a querida da cambalhota no mar: desorientada. 
MAS: 
Poder entrar em um espaço preparado pra atender minhas necessidades é pra mim auto cuidado. Poder de escolha é auto cuidado. 
@casaewa___  obrigada pelo acolhimento que reforça minha auto estima. 
Obrigada por enxergar uma oportunidade de servir a um público que tem recursos de sobra pra cuidar de sua beleza. 
Obrigada @lunaaregina  por capturar essa pérola que foi essa cambalhota marinha.

Hi, I’m Juliana Luna, Luna for short. Citizen of the world. 
Born in Rio de Janeiro, half via Cachoeira-Bahia, living in Lenape Land (Brooklyn) NY for the last 13 years. 

Aries season is here!!! my season y’all! And it has me feeling Bad B*t c h energy. Grateful for all the growth I’ve dedicated myself to so far. 
Grateful for the people all over the world who see me in my most vulnerable places and still wanna ride along. I see you, I love you, thank you.
Grateful for birthing a full wellness practice based in blackness which we named @practicealuna and it’s a gift from my ancestry to the world. 

I’ve been shadow banned on IG for over 2 years now, which has made me lose interest in this platform. But I come around from time to time to say hello. 

Hopefully the people who are still here are taking time for rest and do things that they love and makes them come alive. For me, pole dancing is that aliveness which allows me to move in all the ways that make me feel juicy inside.
I’m also oriented towards fluidity in all aspects of my life. #WaterHasNoEnemy 

Lately I’m learning to live in Radical Aliveness with @wildholyhuman  and it’s hard, and deeply humbling. I am also a priestess (Aluna is an oracle system, 😉 😎 ), yoga and breath work certified and a dedicated student of the Moon. 
I am challenging myself to share more about my inner world, since I’ve been keeping that part of me in secret for quite some time. 🌀 🌪️ ✨🌓✨

Hopefully you can follow along and share some of your own aliveness with me here. Movement is my nature. You’ll see me moving, a lot. Lol

A teacher recently wrote back to me and signed with the following phrase: stay fierce and hurtable.
Those words stuck with me, since the response was to an email in which I described the terror and disappointment of having hard work thrown out the window.
The feeling of rawness has brought me to my knees. To a place where I call everything I have imagined and ask, what now? Can I see the unnamed and unimagined?
How can I stand up in trust after such big disappointment? 
Time and time again I make room for the rumbling fierceness within me and pray that I stay hurtable, since my vulnerability has greater strength than my defeatedness. And it is through that vulnerability that I stay intimate to myself, which opens me up to fully show up and trust another.
Join us for our Monthly Full Moon virtual gathering. Thursday 04/06 8pm EST on Zoom.
We will breathe together and tap into our unnamed and unimagined possibilities.
FREE EVENT - LINK TO SUBSCRIBE IN BIO.

📸 @thaisaquinophotography

We then head to Atins, @lafermedegeorges where we will settle and be welcomed by a delicious farm to table meal. I have been training under a tantric lineage to support my work with Aluna in really being informed by Eros, the emergent current of life force in me/you.

The stillness necessary for trusting our ability to let go... wow! Powerful.

Natural make-up tutorial with Urucum (Bixa Orellana) a native Brazilian tree that produces these gorgeous orange red seeds. 

Thanks to its richness in carotenoids and vitamin E, the urucum fruit has an antioxidant action and thus helps reduce premature skin aging. Its carotenoid content also gives it the power to stimulate the production of melanin, the pigment responsible for tanning (black girl magic). ✨ 

Natural resources are the best way to connect to our sense of being which translates to beauty. 
In Maranhão, Urucum has been used for hundreds of years by traditional healers and indigenous peoples to adorn their bodies and show cultural traits such as language through various designs and symbology painted in diverse ways. It’s our heritage and knowledge of nature that makes us feel deeply connected with all that is. 

Join me @practicealuna retreat to experience the richness of Brazil through direct experience in these pristinely preserved lands.

We are traveling to Atins, Maranhão Nov 26th and have some spots left!
